        "@id": "https://ww3.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=10726"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "CONSTELLATIONS - A Play by Nick Payne"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Staged by Icarus Theatre, one of the leading voices in Toronto's independent theatre scene, CONSTELLATIONS, by Nick Payne, is a two-person play that explores the infinite possibilities of a relationship between a beekeeper (Roland) and a quantum physicist (Marianne) through the lens of multiverse theory, showing how small choices can lead to vastly different outcomes, from love and marriage to heartbreak and illness, all within a non-linear, cyclical structure. Constellations has been staged multiple times on Broadway and in the UK, among other countries, and garnered awards and nominations including Olivier Awards, Drama Desk Awards and a Tony nomination, among dozens of others.</p>\n\n<style>\n    .titleTax {\n       display: none !important;\n   }\n</style>\n\n"
      }
    ],
